cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the archiving of web-native scholarly objects, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of ORCID as a supporting infrastructure for discovery also relates to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR) as it involves the identification and authentication of researchers. Additionally, the analysis of ORCID profiles and their coverage and richness could be considered under social and information networks (cs.SI).
